00:04:24.556 --> 00:04:27.726 A:middle
Shortcuts allow you to provide

00:04:27.856 --> 00:04:29.846 A:middle
dialogues that can be spoken by

00:04:29.846 --> 00:04:31.626 A:middle
Siri, and this gives you the

00:04:31.626 --> 00:04:33.436 A:middle
ability to provide relevant

00:04:33.476 --> 00:04:35.026 A:middle
information, important

00:04:35.026 --> 00:04:38.196 A:middle
information, right with voice.

00:04:38.586 --> 00:04:40.416 A:middle
Fundamentally, shortcuts are --

00:04:40.416 --> 00:04:42.596 A:middle
custom responses are template

00:04:42.596 --> 00:04:44.036 A:middle
strings whose structure you

00:04:44.036 --> 00:04:45.356 A:middle
define in the Intent Definition

00:04:45.356 --> 00:04:45.606 A:middle
File.

00:04:46.056 --> 00:04:49.166 A:middle
And based on the type of

00:04:49.166 --> 00:04:50.866 A:middle
information you provide in your

00:04:50.866 --> 00:04:53.056 A:middle
responses, shortcuts can be one

00:04:53.056 --> 00:04:53.996 A:middle
of four types.

00:04:55.146 --> 00:04:57.786 A:middle
The first is a confirmation

00:04:57.786 --> 00:04:59.196 A:middle
custom response.

00:05:00.876 --> 00:05:02.476 A:middle
This gives you the opportunity

00:05:02.476 --> 00:05:04.166 A:middle
to provide critical information

00:05:04.466 --> 00:05:06.626 A:middle
before your users commit to

00:05:06.626 --> 00:05:07.546 A:middle
running the shortcut.

00:05:07.906 --> 00:05:12.166 A:middle
Next, is a success response.

00:05:12.766 --> 00:05:14.036 A:middle
And it gives you a chance to

00:05:14.036 --> 00:05:16.146 A:middle
provide an auxiliary relevant

00:05:16.146 --> 00:05:17.826 A:middle
information, after the shortcut

00:05:17.826 --> 00:05:19.806 A:middle
has run, and the structure of a

00:05:19.806 --> 00:05:22.146 A:middle
success response consists of

00:05:22.146 --> 00:05:24.596 A:middle
Siri letting the users know that

00:05:24.716 --> 00:05:26.646 A:middle
their order was successful, or

00:05:26.646 --> 00:05:28.046 A:middle
their shortcut ran successfully,

00:05:28.446 --> 00:05:30.176 A:middle
followed by any information that

00:05:30.176 --> 00:05:32.066 A:middle
you provide attributed to your

00:05:32.736 --> 00:05:32.806 A:middle
app.

00:05:34.536 --> 00:05:36.316 A:middle
The third type of custom

00:05:36.316 --> 00:05:38.156 A:middle
response is an informational

00:05:38.156 --> 00:05:38.686 A:middle
response.

00:05:38.796 --> 00:05:41.466 A:middle
And we are really excited about

00:05:42.176 --> 00:05:42.276 A:middle
this.

00:05:42.496 --> 00:05:44.516 A:middle
Informational response allows

00:05:44.516 --> 00:05:46.086 A:middle
you to provide information like

00:05:46.086 --> 00:05:48.986 A:middle
transit schedules or ski

00:05:48.986 --> 00:05:52.606 A:middle
forecast right within Siri, with

00:05:53.186 --> 00:05:53.436 A:middle
voice.

00:05:53.436 --> 00:05:55.076 A:middle
This opens the door for a whole

00:05:55.076 --> 00:05:57.106 A:middle
new category of apps which was

00:05:57.106 --> 00:05:59.296 A:middle
not possible before with Siri.

00:06:00.796 --> 00:06:03.686 A:middle
And finally, when things do not

00:06:03.686 --> 00:06:06.406 A:middle
work as expected, custom error

00:06:06.406 --> 00:06:07.936 A:middle
responses give you the

00:06:07.936 --> 00:06:09.866 A:middle
opportunity to explain what went

00:06:09.866 --> 00:06:11.856 A:middle
wrong instead of just saying,

00:06:12.366 --> 00:06:13.886 A:middle
"Something didn't work."

00:06:14.106 --> 00:06:16.516 A:middle
The structure consists of Siri

00:06:16.516 --> 00:06:18.296 A:middle
communicating to the users that

00:06:18.296 --> 00:06:19.116 A:middle
their intent did not

00:06:19.116 --> 00:06:21.116 A:middle
successfully execute, followed

00:06:21.116 --> 00:06:23.026 A:middle
by information from your app,

00:06:23.026 --> 00:06:24.756 A:middle
and the interaction punctuated

00:06:24.756 --> 00:06:26.696 A:middle
by Siri, advising users to

00:06:26.696 --> 00:06:30.916 A:middle
continue in your apps.

00:06:31.166 --> 00:06:33.336 A:middle
Now, that we understand what

00:06:33.336 --> 00:06:37.186 A:middle
custom responses are, let's take

00:06:37.186 --> 00:06:39.166 A:middle
a look at how you would adopt

00:06:39.166 --> 00:06:41.066 A:middle
them in your apps.

00:06:42.796 --> 00:06:45.526 A:middle
Custom responses work hand in

00:06:45.526 --> 00:06:47.466 A:middle
hand with custom intents.

00:06:48.436 --> 00:06:50.486 A:middle
So, the first step is to define

00:06:50.486 --> 00:06:52.636 A:middle
an intent that models the use

00:06:52.636 --> 00:06:54.056 A:middle
case you are trying to create a

00:06:54.056 --> 00:06:54.746 A:middle
shortcut for.

00:06:56.016 --> 00:06:58.256 A:middle
For Soup Chef, we created an

00:06:58.256 --> 00:07:00.666 A:middle
intent called Order Soup, and it

00:06:58.256 --> 00:07:00.666 A:middle
intent called Order Soup, and it

00:07:00.666 --> 00:07:02.596 A:middle
lets you, you guessed it, order

00:07:02.596 --> 00:07:02.926 A:middle
soup.

00:07:03.226 --> 00:07:08.316 A:middle
Alongside the intent, you have

00:07:08.316 --> 00:07:09.756 A:middle
to pick a category for your

00:07:09.756 --> 00:07:09.986 A:middle
intent.

00:07:10.566 --> 00:07:12.266 A:middle
And the category you pick

00:07:12.876 --> 00:07:14.746 A:middle
influences how Siri speaks about

00:07:14.746 --> 00:07:17.286 A:middle
it or what you see across the OS

00:07:17.286 --> 00:07:18.246 A:middle
like the order buttons.

00:07:19.076 --> 00:07:20.636 A:middle
So, pick something that feels

00:07:20.636 --> 00:07:22.536 A:middle
natural, that works well with

00:07:22.536 --> 00:07:24.846 A:middle
your use case.

00:07:25.046 --> 00:07:26.936 A:middle
Once we have defined our custom

00:07:26.936 --> 00:07:29.166 A:middle
intent, let's go over to the

00:07:29.166 --> 00:07:31.056 A:middle
Responses Tab.

00:07:31.056 --> 00:07:32.706 A:middle
And in the Responses Tab, you

00:07:32.706 --> 00:07:34.166 A:middle
see that we already have a

00:07:34.166 --> 00:07:36.226 A:middle
success and failure response

00:07:36.226 --> 00:07:36.626 A:middle
codes.

00:07:37.106 --> 00:07:38.676 A:middle
But these are just a generic

00:07:38.676 --> 00:07:39.806 A:middle
response codes which don't

00:07:39.806 --> 00:07:41.096 A:middle
convey much more information

00:07:41.096 --> 00:07:42.506 A:middle
besides the status of the

00:07:42.506 --> 00:07:42.996 A:middle
operation.

00:07:43.846 --> 00:07:45.906 A:middle
What I would like to do, is let

00:07:45.906 --> 00:07:48.096 A:middle
our users know how long it will

00:07:48.096 --> 00:07:50.336 A:middle
be until their order is ready

00:07:50.336 --> 00:07:51.446 A:middle
and they can to the store and

00:07:51.446 --> 00:07:51.806 A:middle
pick it up.

