So, what I want to do is define

00:07:54.506 --> 00:07:56.006 A:middle
a custom success response for

00:07:56.086 --> 00:07:56.216 A:middle
that.

00:07:57.186 --> 00:08:00.036 A:middle
Towards that goal, the next step

00:07:57.186 --> 00:08:00.036 A:middle
Towards that goal, the next step

00:08:00.826 --> 00:08:05.436 A:middle
is to declare the response

00:08:05.486 --> 00:08:07.316 A:middle
properties that you will use in

00:08:07.316 --> 00:08:08.566 A:middle
your templates to provide

00:08:08.566 --> 00:08:11.116 A:middle
information at run time.

00:08:11.446 --> 00:08:12.476 A:middle
So, if you go over to the

00:08:12.476 --> 00:08:15.026 A:middle
Properties Section, I'm going to

00:08:15.026 --> 00:08:16.896 A:middle
