00:20:18.136 --> 00:20:21.816 A:middle
And for both NS User Activities

00:20:21.816 --> 00:20:23.426 A:middle
and Intents, there are several

00:20:23.496 --> 00:20:24.226 A:middle
parameters that we can

00:20:24.226 --> 00:20:24.676 A:middle
configure.

00:20:25.886 --> 00:20:27.296 A:middle
The first one is the title.

00:20:28.596 --> 00:20:29.756 A:middle
So, in this case, Order Clam

00:20:29.756 --> 00:20:31.636 A:middle
Chowder, with the subtitle

00:20:31.636 --> 00:20:33.386 A:middle
underneath it and image next to

00:20:33.386 --> 00:20:35.656 A:middle
it, and finally, a suggested

00:20:35.716 --> 00:20:37.126 A:middle
invocation phrase which you'll

00:20:37.126 --> 00:20:37.796 A:middle
get to later.

00:20:39.376 --> 00:20:40.276 A:middle
For each of these, we're going

00:20:40.276 --> 00:20:41.736 A:middle
to go over how best to configure

00:20:41.736 --> 00:20:41.936 A:middle
them.

00:20:42.506 --> 00:20:43.686 A:middle
So, let's get started with the

00:20:43.686 --> 00:20:44.786 A:middle
title and subtitle.

00:20:45.426 --> 00:20:47.496 A:middle
So, when you're thinking about

00:20:47.576 --> 00:20:49.516 A:middle
titles and subtitles, there are

00:20:49.516 --> 00:20:50.626 A:middle
two high-level things that you

00:20:50.626 --> 00:20:51.296 A:middle
should keep in mind.

00:20:52.226 --> 00:20:53.646 A:middle
First, the title should

00:20:53.646 --> 00:20:55.066 A:middle
represent what happens when the

00:20:55.066 --> 00:20:56.376 A:middle
user runs the shortcut.

00:20:56.786 --> 00:20:57.826 A:middle
Your user is going to want to

00:20:57.826 --> 00:20:59.526 A:middle
know exactly what happens before

00:20:59.526 --> 00:21:00.696 A:middle
they run the shortcut or add

00:20:59.526 --> 00:21:00.696 A:middle
they run the shortcut or add

00:21:00.696 --> 00:21:02.166 A:middle
that shortcut to use with Siri.

00:21:02.236 --> 00:21:05.106 A:middle
And secondly, the subtitles will

00:21:05.106 --> 00:21:06.536 A:middle
provide more information, but

00:21:06.536 --> 00:21:07.426 A:middle
only if you need it.

00:21:08.416 --> 00:21:10.036 A:middle
So, let's dive into a little bit

00:21:10.036 --> 00:21:12.306 A:middle
more of the details.

00:21:12.436 --> 00:21:14.136 A:middle
The first easy thing to do is

00:21:14.136 --> 00:21:14.956 A:middle
see a sentence case.

00:21:15.216 --> 00:21:16.626 A:middle
This is to make sure that we

00:21:16.816 --> 00:21:18.486 A:middle
provide a consistent experience

00:21:18.486 --> 00:21:19.876 A:middle
across all different apps and

00:21:19.876 --> 00:21:20.586 A:middle
their shortcuts.

00:21:21.356 --> 00:21:24.266 A:middle
Next, it's important to keep the

00:21:24.266 --> 00:21:24.996 A:middle
title concise.

00:21:25.456 --> 00:21:26.716 A:middle
This is because we're dealing

00:21:26.716 --> 00:21:27.986 A:middle
with potentially a limited

00:21:27.986 --> 00:21:28.856 A:middle
amount of [inaudible].

00:21:28.916 --> 00:21:31.156 A:middle
And you can do this by dropping

00:21:31.156 --> 00:21:32.806 A:middle
articles like "a" and "an" if

00:21:32.806 --> 00:21:34.606 A:middle
your language allows for it.

00:21:35.456 --> 00:21:37.336 A:middle
Next, it's super important to

00:21:37.336 --> 00:21:38.646 A:middle
include critical information.

00:21:38.906 --> 00:21:39.956 A:middle
For example, if you have a

00:21:39.956 --> 00:21:41.816 A:middle
payments app that lets you send

00:21:41.816 --> 00:21:43.186 A:middle
money to your friends and you

00:21:43.186 --> 00:21:44.266 A:middle
have a shortcut for that, it's

00:21:44.266 --> 00:21:45.886 A:middle
important to put the dollar

00:21:45.886 --> 00:21:47.276 A:middle
amount or your currency amount

00:21:47.276 --> 00:21:47.566 A:middle
in that.

00:21:48.146 --> 00:21:50.086 A:middle
Probably in the title in this

00:21:51.516 --> 00:21:51.626 A:middle
case.

00:21:51.846 --> 00:21:53.096 A:middle
Next, if we're working with

00:21:53.096 --> 00:21:54.306 A:middle
Intents, it's important to

00:21:54.306 --> 00:21:55.256 A:middle
include a verb.

00:21:55.416 --> 00:21:56.276 A:middle
And if you're working with

00:21:56.276 --> 00:21:57.496 A:middle
English, we should put that at

00:21:57.496 --> 00:21:58.626 A:middle
the beginning and prepend the

00:21:58.626 --> 00:21:59.766 A:middle
verb to your phrase.

00:21:59.906 --> 00:22:03.076 A:middle
And last but not least, to make

00:21:59.906 --> 00:22:03.076 A:middle
And last but not least, to make

00:22:03.076 --> 00:22:03.906 A:middle
sure that we provide the

00:22:03.966 --> 00:22:05.316 A:middle
shortcuts experience to everyone

00:22:05.316 --> 00:22:06.856 A:middle
around the world, it's very

00:22:06.856 --> 00:22:07.816 A:middle
important to localize.

00:22:08.486 --> 00:22:10.706 A:middle
So, not let's take a look at

00:22:10.746 --> 00:22:11.526 A:middle
some things that we should

00:22:11.526 --> 00:22:11.916 A:middle
avoid.

00:22:12.796 --> 00:22:13.706 A:middle
So, the first thing that we

00:22:13.706 --> 00:22:14.976 A:middle
don't need to include, is the

00:22:14.976 --> 00:22:15.576 A:middle
name of your app.

00:22:16.316 --> 00:22:18.076 A:middle
This is because our RUI already

00:22:18.076 --> 00:22:19.246 A:middle
attributes the name of your app,

00:22:19.246 --> 00:22:20.466 A:middle
and by not including this, you

00:22:20.466 --> 00:22:21.516 A:middle
can save even more space.

00:22:22.126 --> 00:22:25.226 A:middle
And second, we don't need to put

00:22:25.226 --> 00:22:26.496 A:middle
duplicate information in the

00:22:26.496 --> 00:22:27.996 A:middle
title and subtitle for similar

00:22:27.996 --> 00:22:29.656 A:middle
reasons to save space and leave

00:22:29.656 --> 00:22:30.916 A:middle
room for critical information.

00:22:31.456 --> 00:22:34.636 A:middle
And lastly, we don't want to use

00:22:34.636 --> 00:22:36.056 A:middle
quotation marks unless you're

00:22:36.056 --> 00:22:37.156 A:middle
actually quoting something

00:22:37.156 --> 00:22:38.536 A:middle
that's going to be used verbatim

00:22:38.536 --> 00:22:39.176 A:middle
in the shortcut.

00:22:39.526 --> 00:22:40.716 A:middle
For example, if you have a

00:22:40.896 --> 00:22:42.016 A:middle
shortcut to send a message, you

00:22:42.016 --> 00:22:43.096 A:middle
can put the content of the

00:22:43.096 --> 00:22:45.146 A:middle
message in the quotation marks.

00:22:45.216 --> 00:22:48.596 A:middle
So, let's take a look at an

00:22:48.596 --> 00:22:49.106 A:middle
example.

00:22:49.706 --> 00:22:53.446 A:middle
This example says, "A clam

00:22:53.446 --> 00:22:54.476 A:middle
chowder from Soup Chef.

00:22:54.896 --> 00:22:56.306 A:middle
The best way to get soup, Soup

00:22:56.306 --> 00:22:56.676 A:middle
Chef."

00:22:57.736 --> 00:22:59.346 A:middle
And just based on what we

00:22:59.346 --> 00:23:00.476 A:middle
learned about, I think we can

00:22:59.346 --> 00:23:00.476 A:middle
learned about, I think we can

00:23:00.476 --> 00:23:02.076 A:middle
all agree that this is not a

00:23:02.076 --> 00:23:02.806 A:middle
good example.

00:23:03.356 --> 00:23:04.346 A:middle
So, let's try to make it better.

00:23:05.146 --> 00:23:06.706 A:middle
So, the first easy thing that we

00:23:06.706 --> 00:23:08.526 A:middle
can do is to drop the "From Soup

00:23:08.526 --> 00:23:10.146 A:middle
Chef," because as you see, Soup

00:23:10.146 --> 00:23:11.566 A:middle
Chef is already attributed in

00:23:11.566 --> 00:23:11.876 A:middle
this UI.

00:23:12.686 --> 00:23:15.676 A:middle
So, now we have "A Clam

00:23:15.676 --> 00:23:16.016 A:middle
Chowder."

00:23:17.086 --> 00:23:18.176 A:middle
But when I'm looking at this,

00:23:18.346 --> 00:23:19.526 A:middle
I'm not sure what's going to

00:23:19.576 --> 00:23:20.836 A:middle
happen when I run the shortcut.

00:23:20.836 --> 00:23:23.346 A:middle
Am I ordering the soup or just

00:23:23.346 --> 00:23:23.996 A:middle
looking at it?

00:23:24.286 --> 00:23:24.676 A:middle
Who knows?

00:23:25.176 --> 00:23:26.466 A:middle
So, let's fix that by adding a

00:23:26.466 --> 00:23:26.816 A:middle
verb.

00:23:27.466 --> 00:23:28.376 A:middle
And while I'm doing that, I'm

00:23:28.376 --> 00:23:30.076 A:middle
also going to drop the article

00:23:30.076 --> 00:23:34.526 A:middle
"a" to save some space.

00:23:34.726 --> 00:23:36.066 A:middle
So now I have "Order Clam

00:23:36.066 --> 00:23:36.496 A:middle
Chowder."

00:23:37.746 --> 00:23:38.916 A:middle
So, when I'm looking at this,

00:23:38.916 --> 00:23:40.586 A:middle
I'm thinking, "I want to order a

00:23:40.586 --> 00:23:42.176 A:middle
Clam Chowder, not a Clam

00:23:42.256 --> 00:23:43.666 A:middle
Chowder, which doesn't sound

00:23:43.666 --> 00:23:44.926 A:middle
very delicious and we're trying

00:23:44.926 --> 00:23:46.806 A:middle
to sell soup here, so that's

00:23:46.806 --> 00:23:47.996 A:middle
really not ideal.

00:23:48.746 --> 00:23:51.316 A:middle
But the good thing is, we can

00:23:51.366 --> 00:23:52.886 A:middle
fix this really easily by simply

00:23:52.886 --> 00:23:54.206 A:middle
dropping the quotation marks.

00:23:55.466 --> 00:23:56.586 A:middle
And now we have, "Order Clam

00:23:56.586 --> 00:23:56.976 A:middle
Chowder."

00:23:56.976 --> 00:23:58.316 A:middle
And I think at this point, our

00:23:58.466 --> 00:23:59.606 A:middle
title's looking pretty good.

00:24:00.196 --> 00:24:00.996 A:middle
But let's take a look at the

00:24:00.996 --> 00:24:01.536 A:middle
subtitle.

00:24:02.316 --> 00:24:04.136 A:middle
The subtitle says, "The best way

00:24:04.136 --> 00:24:04.756 A:middle
