00:27:43.376 --> 00:27:45.496 A:middle
And as Soup Chef app developers

00:27:45.496 --> 00:27:47.336 A:middle
and general soup enthusiasts, we

00:27:47.336 --> 00:27:48.576 A:middle
think we have some pretty great

00:27:48.576 --> 00:27:50.406 A:middle
ideas on what would make a great

00:27:50.436 --> 00:27:51.226 A:middle
soup ordering phrase.

00:27:51.226 --> 00:27:52.206 A:middle
You know, something like

00:27:52.416 --> 00:27:54.226 A:middle
"Tomato, Tomato" or "Chowder

00:27:54.226 --> 00:27:54.696 A:middle
Time."

00:27:55.686 --> 00:27:57.846 A:middle
So, would it be great if we can

00:27:57.846 --> 00:27:59.476 A:middle
show a suggestion like this?

00:28:00.016 --> 00:28:01.336 A:middle
"Hey user, you can say something

00:28:01.336 --> 00:28:02.546 A:middle
like, 'Chowder Time.'"

00:28:03.186 --> 00:28:04.746 A:middle
And of course, we have an API

00:28:04.746 --> 00:28:05.846 A:middle
for this, so let's take a look.

00:28:06.856 --> 00:28:08.066 A:middle
So, building on a previous

00:28:08.066 --> 00:28:09.596 A:middle
example, all we have to do is

00:28:09.626 --> 00:28:10.586 A:middle
add one line.

00:28:11.336 --> 00:28:12.766 A:middle
So, User Activity has a property

00:28:12.766 --> 00:28:14.246 A:middle
called Suggested Indication

00:28:14.246 --> 00:28:14.516 A:middle
Phrase.

00:28:14.516 --> 00:28:15.666 A:middle
And I'm going to set that to

00:28:15.736 --> 00:28:16.256 A:middle
Chowder Time.

00:28:17.206 --> 00:28:18.576 A:middle
And for Intents, it's the exact

00:28:18.576 --> 00:28:18.996 A:middle
same thing.

00:28:19.786 --> 00:28:21.326 A:middle
Intents also have a property

00:28:21.326 --> 00:28:22.886 A:middle
called Suggested Indication

00:28:22.886 --> 00:28:24.316 A:middle
Phrase which I'll also set to

00:28:24.346 --> 00:28:24.946 A:middle
"Chowder Time."

00:28:25.836 --> 00:28:27.346 A:middle
So, the API for this as you can

00:28:27.346 --> 00:28:28.436 A:middle
see, is super simple.

00:28:28.656 --> 00:28:30.356 A:middle
But what actually makes a good

00:28:30.356 --> 00:28:31.686 A:middle
suggested invocation phrase?

00:28:34.356 --> 00:28:35.896 A:middle
So, the most important thing to

00:28:35.896 --> 00:28:37.596 A:middle
keep in mind is that the

00:28:37.656 --> 00:28:39.246 A:middle
suggested invocation phrase is

00:28:39.246 --> 00:28:40.796 A:middle
both short and memorable.

00:28:41.106 --> 00:28:42.436 A:middle
You have to remember that your

00:28:42.436 --> 00:28:43.326 A:middle
users are going to have to say

00:28:43.326 --> 00:28:45.116 A:middle
this phrase exactly every,

00:28:45.116 --> 00:28:45.966 A:middle
single time they run their

00:28:45.966 --> 00:28:46.436 A:middle
shortcut.

00:28:46.806 --> 00:28:47.736 A:middle
So, ideally it would be

00:28:47.776 --> 00:28:48.876 A:middle
somewhere between two to three

00:28:48.876 --> 00:28:49.330 A:middle
words.

00:28:51.526 --> 00:28:53.016 A:middle
Next, it's important to not

00:28:53.016 --> 00:28:54.846 A:middle
include the phrase, "Hey Siri,"

00:28:54.846 --> 00:28:56.896 A:middle
in your shortcut phrase, because

00:28:57.006 --> 00:28:58.736 A:middle
if your user accidentally sets

00:28:58.736 --> 00:29:00.286 A:middle
their shortcut phrase as "Hey,

00:28:58.736 --> 00:29:00.286 A:middle
their shortcut phrase as "Hey,

00:29:00.286 --> 00:29:01.586 A:middle
Siri, Chowder Time," when they

00:29:01.586 --> 00:29:02.806 A:middle
actually run the shortcut, they

00:29:02.806 --> 00:29:04.166 A:middle
might have to say, "Hey Siri,

00:29:04.166 --> 00:29:06.026 A:middle
Hey Siri, Chowder Time," and no

00:29:06.026 --> 00:29:09.856 A:middle
one wants to do that.

00:29:09.976 --> 00:29:11.206 A:middle
So, let's take a look at some

00:29:11.206 --> 00:29:11.726 A:middle
examples.

00:29:12.286 --> 00:29:15.996 A:middle
This example says, "Hey, Siri,

00:29:15.996 --> 00:29:17.476 A:middle
please place an order, thank

00:29:17.476 --> 00:29:17.646 A:middle
you."

00:29:18.226 --> 00:29:20.936 A:middle
Although this example is polite,

00:29:21.046 --> 00:29:22.976 A:middle
it's not a good example.

00:29:23.806 --> 00:29:25.256 A:middle
First, it contains, "Hey, Siri,"

00:29:25.256 --> 00:29:27.126 A:middle
which is pretty obvious, but

00:29:27.126 --> 00:29:28.356 A:middle
it's a little bit too long for

00:29:28.356 --> 00:29:29.656 A:middle
me to want to repeat it every,

00:29:29.656 --> 00:29:30.796 A:middle
single time I want to run the

00:29:30.856 --> 00:29:31.656 A:middle
shortcut.

00:29:31.656 --> 00:29:32.226 A:middle
So, that's out.

00:29:33.366 --> 00:29:34.316 A:middle
What about this example?

00:29:35.016 --> 00:29:36.766 A:middle
This example says, "Order a clam

00:29:36.766 --> 00:29:38.146 A:middle
chowder to my office."

00:29:38.726 --> 00:29:40.726 A:middle
Seems pretty reasonable, but

00:29:40.726 --> 00:29:42.296 A:middle
this is still not good because

00:29:42.856 --> 00:29:43.836 A:middle
it's still too long.

00:29:43.836 --> 00:29:44.916 A:middle
Like, it's not short and

00:29:44.916 --> 00:29:45.456 A:middle
memorable.

00:29:45.546 --> 00:29:47.176 A:middle
And I don't think I can or want

00:29:47.176 --> 00:29:48.486 A:middle
to remember to say this phrase

00:29:48.696 --> 00:29:50.276 A:middle
every, single time I want clam

00:29:50.276 --> 00:29:51.666 A:middle
chowder delivered to my office.

00:29:53.216 --> 00:29:54.386 A:middle
What about this example?

00:29:55.076 --> 00:29:56.486 A:middle
This simply says, "Chowder

00:29:56.486 --> 00:29:56.776 A:middle
Time."

00:29:57.206 --> 00:29:59.366 A:middle
This is both short and memorable

00:29:59.366 --> 00:30:00.856 A:middle
and doesn't include the phrase,

00:29:59.366 --> 00:30:00.856 A:middle
and doesn't include the phrase,

00:30:00.936 --> 00:30:01.696 A:middle
"Hey, Siri."

00:30:02.056 --> 00:30:03.796 A:middle
So, this passes all of our tests

00:30:03.796 --> 00:30:04.796 A:middle
and that's awesome.

00:30:06.026 --> 00:30:07.366 A:middle
But we can't [inaudible] in

00:30:07.366 --> 00:30:10.416 A:middle
order to provide a truly great

00:30:10.706 --> 00:30:12.116 A:middle
shortcuts experience to your

00:30:12.686 --> 00:30:13.996 A:middle
users, around the world, you

00:30:13.996 --> 00:30:14.756 A:middle
have to make sure it's

00:30:14.756 --> 00:30:15.306 A:middle
localized.

00:30:15.666 --> 00:30:16.906 A:middle
For example, I speak both

00:30:16.906 --> 00:30:18.216 A:middle
English and Japanese, and it

00:30:18.216 --> 00:30:19.646 A:middle
would be great if I can suggest

00:30:20.256 --> 00:30:21.646 A:middle
a Use Shortcuts in Japanese sort

00:30:21.646 --> 00:30:21.976 A:middle
of like this.

00:30:22.056 --> 00:30:24.786 A:middle
So, instead of "Chowder Time," I

00:30:24.786 --> 00:30:26.096 A:middle
can be like [foreign language

00:30:26.736 --> 00:30:27.536 A:middle
spoken] which means, "I'll eat

00:30:27.606 --> 00:30:27.996 A:middle
chowder."

00:30:28.956 --> 00:30:32.306 A:middle
To do this, we can localize.

00:30:32.486 --> 00:30:33.866 A:middle
And when we're thinking about

00:30:33.866 --> 00:30:36.056 A:middle
localization, there are a couple

00:30:36.056 --> 00:30:37.116 A:middle
of things to keep in mind.

00:30:37.526 --> 00:30:39.336 A:middle
So, in addition to localizing

00:30:39.336 --> 00:30:40.556 A:middle
your code, we want to make sure

00:30:40.556 --> 00:30:42.726 A:middle
to localize the content in the

00:30:42.726 --> 00:30:44.216 A:middle
Intent Definition Files, because

00:30:44.216 --> 00:30:45.556 A:middle
as you can remember, there are a

00:30:45.556 --> 00:30:46.506 A:middle
lot of strings in there.

00:30:47.546 --> 00:30:48.976 A:middle
And second, we have to think

00:30:48.976 --> 00:30:49.946 A:middle
about pluralization.

00:30:50.116 --> 00:30:51.246 A:middle
So, even if you're not

00:30:51.246 --> 00:30:52.826 A:middle
localizing to any other language

00:30:52.826 --> 00:30:54.606 A:middle
besides English, if you have to

00:30:54.606 --> 00:30:56.296 A:middle
handle things like, "Order one

00:30:56.296 --> 00:30:57.856 A:middle
clam chowder," versus, "Order

00:30:57.856 --> 00:30:59.356 A:middle
three clam chowders," you have

00:30:59.356 --> 00:31:00.526 A:middle
to think about localization.

00:30:59.356 --> 00:31:00.526 A:middle
to think about localization.

00:31:00.976 --> 00:31:02.866 A:middle
And to learn about all of this

00:31:02.866 --> 00:31:03.506 A:middle
stuff, check out the

00:31:03.506 --> 00:31:05.446 A:middle
Localization Session and their

00:31:05.446 --> 00:31:05.776 A:middle
labs.

00:31:06.126 --> 00:31:07.096 A:middle
They'll teach you everything

00:31:07.096 --> 00:31:08.026 A:middle
that you need to know, and more.

00:31:09.306 --> 00:31:09.646 A:middle
So, cool.

00:31:09.646 --> 00:31:11.346 A:middle
For now, let's go back to

00:31:11.376 --> 00:31:11.666 A:middle
English.

00:31:12.386 --> 00:31:15.306 A:middle
Now, that we've followed these

00:31:15.566 --> 00:31:16.856 A:middle
best practices, when we go to

00:31:16.856 --> 00:31:17.606 A:middle
the Settings UI, you are

00:31:17.706 --> 00:31:19.526 A:middle
presented with a beautiful list

00:31:19.566 --> 00:31:20.836 A:middle
of suggested shortcuts.

00:31:21.356 --> 00:31:22.916 A:middle
And right now, these are based

00:31:22.916 --> 00:31:24.906 A:middle
on a combination of suggestions

00:31:24.906 --> 00:31:26.056 A:middle
based on the user's past

00:31:26.056 --> 00:31:27.276 A:middle
routines and the things that the

00:31:27.276 --> 00:31:28.196 A:middle
user did recently.

00:31:29.126 --> 00:31:30.686 A:middle
But in addition, we provide an

00:31:30.686 --> 00:31:32.356 A:middle
API to allow developers to

00:31:32.356 --> 00:31:33.676 A:middle
suggest their own shortcuts.

00:31:34.176 --> 00:31:35.456 A:middle
And this is useful because this

00:31:35.456 --> 00:31:36.856 A:middle
allows you to suggest things for

00:31:36.856 --> 00:31:37.886 A:middle
things that the user hasn't

00:31:37.886 --> 00:31:39.536 A:middle
necessarily done yet or hasn't

00:31:39.536 --> 00:31:40.126 A:middle
done recently.

00:31:40.836 --> 00:31:42.326 A:middle
For example, if you have a music

00:31:42.326 --> 00:31:43.936 A:middle
app, you might want to offer a

00:31:44.026 --> 00:31:45.366 A:middle
shortcut for playing a

00:31:45.366 --> 00:31:46.726 A:middle
particular playlist, even if the

00:31:46.726 --> 00:31:48.206 A:middle
user hasn't played it before or

00:31:48.206 --> 00:31:49.216 A:middle
hasn't played it recently,

00:31:49.466 --> 00:31:51.566 A:middle
because presumably, if a user

00:31:51.566 --> 00:31:52.786 A:middle
has created the playlist, they

00:31:52.786 --> 00:31:53.786 A:middle
probably ought to play it at

00:31:53.856 --> 00:31:54.646 A:middle
some point in the future.

00:31:55.246 --> 00:31:57.476 A:middle
So, in the Soup Chef app, I

00:31:57.476 --> 00:31:58.796 A:middle
think it'd be great if we can

00:31:58.796 --> 00:32:01.236 A:middle
suggest a shortcut for ordering

00:31:58.796 --> 00:32:01.236 A:middle
suggest a shortcut for ordering

00:32:01.236 --> 00:32:02.726 A:middle
the soup of the day, even if

00:32:02.726 --> 00:32:03.446 A:middle
they haven't ordered it

00:32:03.446 --> 00:32:04.696 A:middle
recently, or have never ordered

00:32:04.696 --> 00:32:06.336 A:middle
it, because based on past

00:32:06.336 --> 00:32:07.736 A:middle
experience, our users seem to

00:32:07.736 --> 00:32:09.066 A:middle
love it because it's both

00:32:09.066 --> 00:32:10.276 A:middle
delicious and offered at a

00:32:10.276 --> 00:32:10.966 A:middle
special price.

00:32:11.736 --> 00:32:13.466 A:middle
So, let's take a look at the API

00:32:13.586 --> 00:32:15.906 A:middle
on how to do this.

00:32:16.036 --> 00:32:19.056 A:middle
So, for Intents, you can create

00:32:19.056 --> 00:32:20.226 A:middle
an IN Shortcut out of Intent,

00:32:20.506 --> 00:32:21.946 A:middle
well, and for User Activities,

00:32:21.946 --> 00:32:23.056 A:middle
you can also create an IN

00:32:23.056 --> 00:32:23.816 A:middle
Shortcut out of it.

00:32:23.816 --> 00:32:25.166 A:middle
I'm going to wrap it in a

00:32:25.166 --> 00:32:27.146 A:middle
suggestions list and pass it

00:32:27.146 --> 00:32:28.726 A:middle
into IN Voice Shortcut Centers

00:32:29.026 --> 00:32:31.126 A:middle
Set Shortcut Suggestions Method.

00:32:32.116 --> 00:32:33.766 A:middle
And once you do that, you'll see

00:32:34.136 --> 00:32:36.486 A:middle
my suggestions alongside all the

00:32:36.486 --> 00:32:38.006 A:middle
other system's suggestions.

00:32:38.796 --> 00:32:40.286 A:middle
And by the way, the same set of

00:32:40.486 --> 00:32:42.286 A:middle
suggestions is shown in the

00:32:42.346 --> 00:32:43.936 A:middle
shortcuts app, so you can create

00:32:43.936 --> 00:32:45.416 A:middle
custom shortcuts, using your

00:32:45.416 --> 00:32:45.926 A:middle
shortcuts.

00:32:49.496 --> 00:32:52.236 A:middle
So, now that we put in all this

00:32:52.236 --> 00:32:54.336 A:middle
work to provide a great voice

00:32:54.336 --> 00:32:55.766 A:middle
experience for your users, we

00:32:55.976 --> 00:32:56.976 A:middle
want to make sure that your

00:32:56.976 --> 00:32:58.566 A:middle
users know that they can add

00:32:58.826 --> 00:33:00.366 A:middle
shortcuts to use with Siri.

00:32:58.826 --> 00:33:00.366 A:middle
shortcuts to use with Siri.

00:33:00.486 --> 00:33:02.016 A:middle
And the best way to do that is

00:33:02.106 --> 00:33:03.716 A:middle
bringing shortcuts into your

00:33:03.716 --> 00:33:05.806 A:middle
app, so that users can create

00:33:05.806 --> 00:33:07.676 A:middle
shortcuts right from inside your

00:33:08.016 --> 00:33:08.086 A:middle
app.

00:33:09.316 --> 00:33:11.556 A:middle
So, for example, I just ordered

00:33:11.556 --> 00:33:14.396 A:middle
a soup, and I'm going to need a

00:33:14.396 --> 00:33:16.316 A:middle
suggestion to add this to Siri.

00:33:16.916 --> 00:33:20.286 A:middle
And when I tap, "Add to Siri,"

